        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:21PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 520 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Huletts Landing, or 8 miles northwest of Whitehall, moving east at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lock Twelve Marina, Shelving Rock, Putnam, Dresden Center, Low
Hampton, Putnam Station, Silver Bay, Snody Dock, Clemons, Sabbath Day
Point, Hampton Flats, Hague, Huletts Landing, Ottenburgs Ramp, and
Whitehall.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
